article.headline: East Tenn. St. 76, Wofford 54
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Zakee Wadood scored 17 points to lead five East Tennessee State players in double figures and the Bucs remained unbeaten in conference play with a 76-54 victory Wednesday night over Wofford. The Bucs (16-4, 8-0 Southern Conference) went on a 22-0 run early in the game to erase a five-point deficit and take a 24-7 lead with 11:51 left in the opening half. ETSU never looked back and took a 45-29 lead into the locker room. James Anthony and Brad Nuckles both scored 13 points for ETSU, with Anthony also grabbing seven rebounds. Tim Smith added 12 points and Jerald Fields 11 as the Bucs shot 47 percent from the field. Tyler Berg had 12 points and 11 rebounds for the Terriers (6-12, 2-5), who shot just 34 percent and had 21 turnovers. Howard Wilkerson had 10 points for Wofford. The Terriers cut ETSU's lead to 47-37 with 16:35 left before the Bucs went on a 8-0 run to put the game away for good.
